Gordon,

Thanks for the quick reply on the last post.

It is from a backup file off tape, so the recover.gz was likely being
written to when the tape backup was done.
Since I hit the java gzip error my own choice is to use gunzip to
uncompress and then point the new job to the uncompressed file. If I
try to uncompress using gunzip I get the &#39;unzip: recover.gz:
unexpected end of file&#39; error. I believe I have found a solution while
reviewing the &#39;man gunzip&#39; entry.

file:  Corrupt input. Use gzcat to recover some data.
                     gzcat file &gt; recover

If I use gzcat recover.gz &gt; recover.log then I beleive I can get the
output up to the error.

Is this how you have got around this problem before?

Mike

